    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Teriyaki Chicken</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 boneless, skinless chicken thighs</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>1/2 cup soy sauce</li>
            <li>1/4 cup mirin (sweet rice wine)</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons sake (Japanese rice wine)</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons sugar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon vegetable oil</li>
            <li>Sesame seeds and green onions, for garnish</li>
            <li>Steamed rice, for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Teriyaki Chicken</li>
            <li>Japanese</li>
            <li>Chicken</li>
            <li>Main Course</li>
            <li>Easy</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Season the chicken thighs with salt and black pepper.</li>
            <li>In a bowl, whisk together soy sauce, mirin, sake, and sugar to create the teriyaki sauce.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken thighs and cook until browned on both sides.</li>
            <li>Pour the teriyaki sauce over the chicken and simmer until the sauce thickens and the chicken is cooked through.</li>
            <li>Transfer the teriyaki chicken to a serving plate, garnish with sesame seeds and sliced green onions.</li>
            <li>Serve over steamed rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious homemade Teriyaki Chicken!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

